Popular actor Lateef Adedimeji has bagged an international award in U.S. over his lead role in the ‘Ayinla’ soar-away movie. Adedemeji announced his latest achievement at the recently held Hollywood and African Prestigious Awards (HAPA) award. The movie star, who expressed immense joy for getting a lead role in “Ayinla” after having prayed for a cameo role in any of Tunde Kelani’s films, celebrated being honoured with an award as “Best Actor” in a film; alongside Ramsey Nouah and Etinosa Idemudia. Sharing photos from the event which took place in the U.S, Adedemeji appreciated the award’s organisers’ for honouring him as well as acknowledged his colleagues not forgetting the film maker, Tunde Kelani.   I miss Prophet T.B Joshua, says Yul Edochie     Wife sweetest thing that can never cause me diabetes –…     Davido reportedly eyes Lori Harvey   “Best Actor in a film! AYINLA! Thank you! I was honored last night at a private dinner with the Founder and Chief Executive Officer/ Executive Producer, Hollywood and African Prestigious Awards, Ms Tina Weisinger. “With my boss @ramseynouah and beautiful @etinosaofficial in the filming industry as the Best Africa Male Actor from U.S. “Thank you @hapawards, thank you babami @tkelani, thank you my ever gallant @jadeosiberu,’’ he wrote.